                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>1<lb/></p>
            <p>Hon. Joseph Blumenthal opened the convention held at<lb/> Room 24&#44; Cooper Institute at 3 P. M.&#44; and introduced<lb/> Rev. Dr F. de Sola Mendes who uttered an impressive<lb/> prayer.<lb/></p>
            <p>Credentials of delegates from contributing congregations were<lb/> then presented and referred to a committee composed of<lb/> J. E. Newburger&#44; J. E. Phillips &#38; Isaac Fles.  Following<lb/> is a list of the congregations represented&#58; Adath Jeshurun&#44;<lb/> Phila.&#59; Hon. Emanuel Furth &#40;proxy for Jacob Singer&#41;<lb/> Ahaneth Chesed&#44; N. Y.&#59; Louis Asch&#44; Marx Ottinger&#44; M. S. Barnet&#44;<lb/> Solomon Simms&#44; Solomon Body &#38; David Greenfeld&#59;<lb/> Anshe Emeth&#44; Phila&#44; Pa.&#59; M. I. Asch&#59; Bikur Cholim<lb/> Balt. Md. Dr. A. Friedenwald&#59; Bnai Israel&#44; N. Y. Isaac Fles<lb/> and Dr. D. Brekes&#59; Bnai Israel&#44; Galveston&#44; Texas&#59; Bnai<lb/> Jeshurun&#44; N. Y. Rev. H. S. Jacob &#40;unavoidably absent&#41; and<lb/> Newman Cowen&#59; Bnai Sholom&#44; New Haven&#44; Conn. Rabbi<lb/> Wilbur&#59; Chizuk Amuno&#44; Balt. Md. Rev. Dr. H. W. Schneeberger<lb/> &#38; Dr. A. Friedenwald&#59; Derech Amuno&#44; N. Y. Nathan Lenin&#59;<lb/> Etz Chayim&#44; Pittsburgh&#44; Pa. Kehillath Jeshurun&#44; N. Y.<lb/> Mickve Israel&#44; Phila&#44; Pa. Rev. Dr. S. Morais&#44; Dr. S. Solis Cohen<lb/> and S. M. Hyneman&#59; Montefiore Cong. N. Y. Rev. Moses Guedalia&#59;<lb/> &#91;&#63;&#93; Isedek&#44; San Francisco&#44; Cal. Rodef Sholom&#44; N. Y.<lb/> Rev. Dr. A. Wise and Joseph E. Newburger&#59; Rodef Sholom&#44;<lb/> Phila&#44; Pa&#59; Benj. I. Teller&#44; Edward L. Rothschild and<lb/> Jacob Miller.  Shearith Israel&#44; Balt. Dr. Aaron Friedenwald&#59;<lb/> Shearith Israel&#44; N. Y. &#40;19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St&#41; D. M. Piza&#44; Rev. Dr. H. P. Mendes&#44;<lb/> Hon. Joseph Blumenthal&#44; J. Edgar Phillips&#44; Lewis Hyman and<lb/> David De Meza&#59; Shearith Israel&#44; N. Y. &#40;On. C.&#41; Shaarez<lb/> Tefiln&#44; N. Y. Rev. Dr F. de Sola Mendes.  Beth Hanedeash Hagodol&#44; N. Y.<lb/> J. Jones&#59; Beth Hanedeash&#44; N. Y. S. Jermalowski&#59; Adath Israel&#44; N. Y. Joseph Arthur<lb/> Levy.  The President of the Board of Trustees then read the following report which<lb/> was enthusiastically received and widely applauded&#59;<lb/> Here insert Pres. report<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>2<lb/></p>
            <p>The nominating committee reported the following officers for the convention who<lb/> were unanimously elected&#58; Pres. Hon. J. Blumenthal&#44; 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> Vice&#45;President<lb/> <del>Mr</del> David Greenfeld&#59; 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> V. Pres. Dr. A. Friedenwald and secretaries&#59;<lb/> J. E. Newburger and Hon. Emanuel Furth.<lb/></p>
            <p>The report of the Board of Trustees for the two years just past was then<lb/> read by J. E. Newburger&#44; secretary of the Board.  The report showed<lb/> that the receipt from divds&#44; congregations&#44; patrons &#38; subscribers had been<lb/> 8370.39&#44; which the expenditures had been 2233.27&#44; leaving a balance of<lb/> &#36;6137.12&#44; of which &#36;5000 had been set aside as a sinking fund&#44;<lb/> since the closing of the accounts on Jan. 15&#44; &#36;716 additional had<lb/> been received.  There are now in the seminary pursuing regular<lb/> instruction&#59; in the Preparatory Class 10 admitted 1 attending without regular<lb/> admission and 3 applicants&#59; in the Junior Class 4 admitted 4 attending<lb/> without reg. admission &#38; 2 applicants.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais&#44; President of the Faculty then read the report on the scholastic<lb/> affairs of the seminary during the year <del>an</del> since it was spared<lb/></p>
            <p>Here insert of Dr Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>The terms of the 5 trustees of the third class having expired an election took<lb/> place which resulted in the unanimous choice of the brothers<lb/> Levin&#44; Isaac Fles&#44; Louis Asch&#44; Jonas Weil and Henry Richter as<lb/> Trustees to serve for six years.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dr. S. Solis Cohen&#44; Joseph E. Newburger and Hon. Emanuel Furth<lb/> introduced an amendment to the Constitution&#44; which will change the number<lb/> necessary to form a quorum for the Board of Trustees from eight to seven&#59;<lb/> increase the number of Trustees from fifteen to twenty one&#44; and make the<lb/> Trustees delegates ex&#45;officio.  The amendment will be acted on at the<lb/> next convention.<lb/></p>
            <p>A vote of thanks was tendered to the officers of the convention for the<lb/> able manner in which they had discharged their duties.<lb/></p>
            <p>A fervent closing prayer was delivered by Rev. Dr. H W Schneeberger<lb/></p>
